<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1010" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1010">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 703.3212/23.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 1, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>265. Your September 29. The strain upon you has been so great that we
                            appreciate your need of a vacation and rest, and shall approve of your
                            course in leaving whenever you feel that you should go. We are glad,
                            however, that you think it wise and possible to remain until the present
                            situation clears up. We shall be pleased to follow your wishes in regard
                            to a representative during your absence. Matters might be left with your
                            Chargé, who, as the head of your Legation, could represent us, acting in
                            conjunction with Silliman or some other American as an adviser.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>